document_data.History:
Artemis was born alongside her twin brother [[Apollo]] by the [[Greater Titan]] [[Leto]] and [[Zeus]].<ref>{{Cite dragon/153/The Goals of the Gods|17}}

In a land that consisted of a [[Wikipedia:Ancient Greece|collection of city-states]],{{Cite dragon/58/Four myths from Greece|21}} the same land that some early planar immigrants to [[Toril]] would later hail from, Artemis alongside her twin brother taught the man known as [[Chiron]] the arts of hunting and medicine, whose fame and skill in those fields became revered by deities and mortals alike over time.

At some point a group of [[adventurer]]s on Toril came to the island of [[Achea]] and ascended it, bringing them into the plane of Olympus. The Olympian Hermes took notice of them and decided to have a bit of fun, disguising himself as a wizened shepherd and making up a backstory that Artemis sentenced him to forever wander Olympus after he mistended his flock.

At another point, an adventuring company from Toril called the [[Company of the Swan]] found themselves on Olympus after their [[wizard]] [[Wemick|Wemick the Wise]] botched a casting of ''teleport without error''. After traveling down mountainside for {{SI|4|mile|long=yes}} they came across a cave, with an old hermit mage inside that called out to them using ''[[ventriloquism]]'' to enter. The hermit introduced himself as Jerraman, though much like what occured for the aforementioned group of adventurers, this was in actuality the Olympian god Hermes in disguise. After explaining to him how they got there,{{Cite polyhedron/72/Experience Preferred, Part One|12-13}}<ref group="note" name="Realms">Although written as a setting-neutral adventure, the [[AD&D_Trading_Cards#1993_series|1993 series of AD&D Trading Cards]] places player characters [[Matilda|Matilda the White Lady]], [[Ada the Unbending]], [[Ratha Rann|Ratha Rann the Eagle-Eyed]], [[Sagrais Bigelow]], [[Henry|Henry the Shadow Master]], and [[Wemick|Wemick the Wise]] in the Forgotten Realms. Jerraman offered the Company of the Swan a [[scroll]] of ''teleport without error'' if they could in return retrieve for him one of the arrows from the quiver of Artemis.<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/73/Experience Preferred, Part Two|7}}

During their time in Olympus, trecking through the forest of Artemis, the adventurers never encountered the goddess herself. After rescuing a [[dryad]] from six [[minotaur]]s, they were informed by her that the forest they were in was so large that she hadn't seen Artemis in those parts for decades. Desperate for the ''scroll of teleport without error'' that was offered to them, the Company of the Swan sought out a [[medusa]] mage in the woods named [[Gharleee]], who had two arrows of The Huntress in her possession.{{Cite polyhedron/72/Experience Preferred, Part One|14}} Eventually, whether by cooperating with or slaying the medusa, the Company of the Swan retrieved the arrows and earned the scroll that was promised them, allowing them to leave Olympus.<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/72/Experience Preferred, Part One|15}}
